                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d574">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/5436: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé at Tangier</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Childs</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tangier</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-11T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 11, 1942—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 11—2:51 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>214. My 195, May 5, 8 p.m. Following repeated inquiries High Commissariat has now
                    telephoned to state that reference in the second paragraph of General Orgaz’
                    note is to the interview had on April 11.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Madrid.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Childs</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
